block content
  p Giphy serves!{' '}
    span.bold 7 billion
    |!{' '}GIFs and stickers to!{' '}
    span.bold 500 million
    |!{' '}people every single day. Their API powers pretty much every messaging app out there: Facebook, Instagram, Snap, Tik Tok, etc.
  p This has opened up quite a novel way for brands to get exposure. All you need is a free!{' '}
    a(href="https://support.giphy.com/hc/en-us/articles/360019977992-Apply-For-A-Brand-Channel") Giphy brand channel
    | . Then any GIF or sticker you upload is publically available on Giphy's search engine. And nothing is stopping you slipping in your logo, product or even URL.
  p Let's run through an example
  h2 Karla and Co.
  p Karla and Co. is a small, Latina clothing brand ran by Karla and her husband Brian. Since August they’ve uploaded 16 stickers to Giphy pulling in around 100,000 views each day:
  img(src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/giphy4.png" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__85
  p The first step is creating GIFs which match what your audience might search for. For Karla it's phrases like “Latina vibes” or “Ay Mama”. Next, you slip in their URL and upload to Giphy tagging relevant keywords.
  p Once you have 5 GIFs you can apply for a brand channel and then your GIFs are publicly available and can be found on any messaging platform:
  video(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/bb2.mp4" class="img__50" playsinline="playsinline" controls)
